ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa says ANC Youth League members should model themselves after founding President Peter Mokaba. eNCA reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones was there. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa says ANC Youth League members should model themselves after Peter Mokaba, the late ANC youth league leader and struggle stalwart. The president chastised youth leadership for their lack of discipline. This after his keynote address was delayed by battles over accreditation. READ: ANCYL members protest over memorial lecture access The president eventually spoke outside the Jack Botes Hall in Polokwane. Ramaphosa said he's inspired by some of the proposals being made by youth in Limpopo to tackle unemployment and skills shortages. He also said ANCYL members should be at the forefront of free education.